content:
I am trying to provide the same content inside two different base files in Django using the "extends" and "include" template tags. I have two files, page1.html and page2.html, which extend base1.html and base2.html respectively, and include commondata.html. The commondata.html overrides a block that is specified in both base1.html and base2.html. However, I am unable to use both extends and include simultaneously. Is there a workaround to this issue? My ultimate goal is to provide the same page in both PDF and HTML format, where the formatting is slightly different.

page1.html:
```
{% extends "base1.html" %}
{% include "commondata.html" %}
```
page2.html:
```
{% extends "base2.html" %} 
{% include "commondata.html" %}
```
